*bmon-2.1.0-r2 (10 Sep 2005)

  10 Sep 2005; Marcelo Goes <vanquirius@gentoo.org> -bmon-2.1.0-r1.ebuild,
  +bmon-2.1.0-r2.ebuild:
  Revision bump since installed contents have changed. Also, sed line is no
  longer necessary.

  10 Sep 2005; Marcelo Goes <vanquirius@gentoo.org>
  -files/libnl-0.5.0-include.diff, bmon-2.1.0-r1.ebuild:
  Broke off libnl from bmon, it is now provided by dev-libs/libnl. Dropped all
  keywords except x86 because of this, opening a new bug to get things
  keyworded properly again.

  10 Sep 2005; Marcelo Goes <vanquirius@gentoo.org> bmon-2.1.0-r1.ebuild:
  Add dbi USE flag, which DEPENDs on dev-db/libdbi and activates support for
  it and rrdtool USE flag, which DEPENDs on net-analyzer/rrdtool and actives
  librrd support. Forced to drop hppa and sparc because of libdbi dependency.

  09 Sep 2005; Marcelo Goes <vanquirius@gentoo.org>
  +files/bmon-2.1.0-gcc4.diff, bmon-2.1.0-r1.ebuild:
  Add gcc4 patch for bug 105343. Thanks to Anatoly Kamchatnov <rev@male.ru>
  for reporting.

